  "prompt": "I am graduating in may 2018, should I apply for CDS 1 of 2017?",
  "response": "The Combined Defence Services (CDS) examination is conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) twice a year (CDS I and CDS II) to recruit candidates into the Indian Military Academy, Officers Training Academy, Indian Naval Academy, and Indian Air Force Academy.\n\n### Should you apply for CDS I of 2017 if you are graduating in May 2018?\nThe eligibility criteria for the CDS exam depend on the academy you are applying for:\n\n1. **Indian Military Academy (IMA)** and **Officers Training Academy (OTA)**:  \n   - You must be a graduate (in any discipline) from a recognized university.  \n   - Since you are graduating in May 2018, you will not have completed your degree by the time of the CDS I 2017 exam (February 2018). Therefore, you are **not eligible** for IMA or OTA in CDS I 2017.\n\n2. **Indian Naval Academy (INA)** and **Indian Air Force Academy (AFA)**:  \n   - For INA and AFA, specific educational qualifications are required (e.g., Engineering degree for INA or a degree with Physics and Mathematics for AFA).  \n   - Again, since you will not have completed your degree by the time of the CDS I 2017 exam, you are **not eligible** for these academies either.\n\n### What should you do?\nYou should apply for **CDS II 2018**, which typically takes place in November 2018. By then, you would have graduated and met the eligibility criteria. The notification for CDS II 2018 is usually released in August 2018.\n\n### Key Points:\n- You cannot apply for CDS I 2017 because you will not have completed your degree by the time of the exam.\n- Plan to apply for CDS II 2018 after you graduate in May 2018.\n- Use the time between now and the CDS II 2018 exam to prepare thoroughly for the written exam and SSB interview.\n\nGood luck with your graduation and future endeavors!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
